y internet. Lingel outlines actions that internet activists and everyday users can take to defend and secure more protections for the individual and to carve out more spaces of freedom for the people—not businesses—online.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aDigital divide. 0aInternetxSocial aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Technology Studies.2bisacsh  aUser.  aaccessible.  aactivism.  aagency.  acommunication.  aconnection.  aculture.  adata.  ademocratic.  adigital harassment.  aequitable.  afake news.  ahyper commercialization.  ainfrastructure.  aisolation.  aliteracy.  amedia studies.  aonline.  aparticipation costs.  apolitics.  apower struggle.  asocial media.  aspace.  atech industry.  atoolkit.  avocabulary.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2021 Englishz978311075406308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2021z9783110753950oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073915240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052097570540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520975705423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520975705/original  a978-3-11-073915-2  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075406-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-SEWb2021